  "fixtext": {
    "text": "Configure the operating system to prevent a user from overriding a screensaver lock after a 15-minute period of inactivity for graphical user interfaces.\n\nCreate a database to contain the system-wide screensaver settings (if it does not already exist) with the following command: \n\nNote: The example below is using the database \"local\" for the system, so if the system is using another database in \"/etc/dconf/profile/user\", the file should be created under the appropriate subdirectory.\n\n# touch /etc/dconf/db/local.d/locks/session\n\nAdd the setting to lock the screensaver lock delay:\n\n/org/gnome/desktop/screensaver/lock-delay",
    "lang": "en",
