      "text": "SV-86831",
      "system": "http://cyber.mil/legacy"
    },
    {
      "text": "CCI-000172",
      "system": "http://cyber.mil/cci"
    },
    {
      "text": "CCI-002884",
      "system": "http://cyber.mil/cci"
    }
  ],
  "fixtext": {
    "text": "Configure the operating system to generate audit records when successful/unsuccessful attempts to use the \"unlinkat\" syscall occur.\n\nAdd the following rules in \"/etc/audit/rules.d/audit.rules\":\n\n-a always,exit -F arch=b32 -S unlinkat -F auid&gt;=1000 -F auid!=unset -k delete\n\n-a always,exit -F arch=b64 -S unlinkat -F auid&gt;=1000 -F auid!=unset -k delete\n\nThe audit daemon must be restarted for the changes to take effect.",
    "lang": "en",
    "fixref": "F-4697r462688_fix"
  },
  "fix": {
    "id": "F-4697r462688_fix"
  },
  "check": {
    "check-content-ref": {
      "name": "oval:mil.disa.stig.rhel7:def:627",
